        15
      ],
      "anchor_refs": [
        "Berakhot 62b:16"
      ],
      "hebrew": "וְלָקַחְתָּ֞ אֶת־כֶּ֣סֶף הַכִּפֻּרִ֗ים מֵאֵת֙ בְּנֵ֣י יִשְׂרָאֵ֔ל וְנָתַתָּ֣ אֹת֔וֹ עַל־עֲבֹדַ֖ת אֹ֣הֶל מוֹעֵ֑ד וְהָיָה֩ לִבְנֵ֨י יִשְׂרָאֵ֤ל לְזִכָּרוֹן֙ לִפְנֵ֣י יְהֹוָ֔ה לְכַפֵּ֖ר עַל־נַפְשֹׁתֵיכֶֽם׃&nbsp;<span class=\"mam-spi-pe\">{פ}</span><br>",
      "english": "You shall take the expiation money from the Israelites and assign it to the service of the Tent of Meeting; it shall serve the Israelites as a reminder before G<small>OD</small>, as expiation for your persons.",
      "marker_line_index": 39,
      "placement_method": "quote_match",
      "placement_score": 25,
      "matched_snippet": "ולקחת את כסף הכפורים מאת בני ישראל וגו",
      "source_kind": "direct_quote"
    },
    {
      "ref": "Genesis 22:14",
      "he_ref": "בראשית כ״ב:י״ד",
      "url": "https://www.sefaria.org/Genesis_22%3A14?lang=bi",
      "segment_ids": [
        15,
        16
      ],
      "anchor_refs": [
        "Berakhot 62b:16",
        "Berakhot 62b:17"
      ],
      "hebrew": "וַיִּקְרָ֧א אַבְרָהָ֛ם שֵֽׁם־הַמָּק֥וֹם הַה֖וּא יְהֹוָ֣ה&thinsp;<small>׀</small>&thinsp;יִרְאֶ֑ה אֲשֶׁר֙ יֵאָמֵ֣ר הַיּ֔וֹם בְּהַ֥ר יְהֹוָ֖ה יֵרָאֶֽה׃",
      "english": "And Abraham named that site Adonai-yireh,<sup class=\"footnote-marker\">d</sup><i class=\"footnote\"><b>Adonai-yireh </b>I.e., “G<small>OD</small> will see” or “G<small>OD</small> takes care”; cf. v. <a class=\"refLink\" data-ref=\"Genesis 22:8\" href=\"Genesis.22.8\">8</a>.</i> whence the present saying, “On G<small>OD</small>’s mount there is vision.”<sup class=\"footnote-marker\">e</sup><i class=\"footnote\"><b>On G<small>OD</small>’s mount there is vision </b>Heb. <i>be-har y-h-w-h yeraʼeh</i>. Or “…there is contact”; cf. note at <a class=\"refLink\" data-ref=\"Genesis 12:7\" href=\"Genesis.12.7\">12.7</a>.</i>",
      "marker_line_index": 40,
      "placement_method": "quote_match",
      "placement_score": 4,
      "matched_snippet": "בהר ה יראה",
      "source_kind": "direct_quote"
    },
    {
      "ref": "Ezekiel 46:9",
      "he_ref": "יחזקאל מ״ו:ט׳",
      "url": "https://www.sefaria.org/Ezekiel_46%3A9?lang=bi",
      "segment_ids": [
        18
      ],
      "anchor_refs": [
        "Berakhot 62b:19"
      ],
      "hebrew": "וּבְב֨וֹא עַם־הָאָ֜רֶץ לִפְנֵ֣י יְהֹוָה֮ בַּמּוֹעֲדִים֒ הַבָּ֡א דֶּרֶךְ־שַׁ֨עַר צָפ֜וֹן לְהִֽשְׁתַּחֲוֺ֗ת יֵצֵא֙ דֶּרֶךְ־שַׁ֣עַר נֶ֔גֶב וְהַבָּא֙ דֶּרֶךְ־שַׁ֣עַר נֶ֔גֶב יֵצֵ֖א דֶּרֶךְ־שַׁ֣עַר צָפ֑וֹנָה לֹ֣א יָשׁ֗וּב דֶּ֤רֶךְ הַשַּׁ֙עַר֙ אֲשֶׁר־בָּ֣א ב֔וֹ כִּ֥י נִכְח֖וֹ <span class=\"mam-kq\"><span class=\"mam-kq-k\">(יצאו)</span> <span class=\"mam-kq-q\">[יֵצֵֽא]</span></span>׃",
      "english": "But on the fixed occasions, when the common people come before G<small>OD</small>, whoever enters by the north gate to bow low shall leave by the south gate; and whoever enters by the south gate shall leave by the north gate. They shall not go back through the gate by which they came in, but shall go out by the opposite one.<sup class=\"footnote-marker\">b</sup><i class=\"footnote\"><b>by the opposite one </b>Lit. “straight before him.”</i>",
      "marker_line_index": 47,
      "placement_method": "quote_match",
      "placement_score": 9,
      "matched_snippet": "ובבא עם הארץ לפני ה במועדים וגו",
      "source_kind": "direct_quote"
    },
    {
      "ref": "Exodus 3:5",
      "he_ref": "שמות ג׳:ה׳",
